CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1951, pg. 32 reads: "Pitt's Educators, Soldiers, Teachers, Chemists, Engineers - Left photo, left to right: Richard S. Richards, Virginia Elaine Hall, Robert McCoy Higginbotham, Imogene R. Perrin, and D. Herbert Wallace graduated form the College at the University of Pittsburgh. Higginbotham and Wallace were commissioned second lieutenants in Air Corps Reserve.  Wallace was one of the eleven new officers who gained their commissions with the designation: "Distinguished Military Graduate."..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of University of Pittsburgh graduates, from left: Richard S. Richards, Virginia Elaine Hall, Robert McCoy Higginbotham, Imogene R. Perrin, and D. Herbert Wallace, posed on lawn outside of Syria Mosque, Oakland
